# OlonJS Monorepo (npm-jpcore)

AI-native content infrastructure for Vercel & Vite. Deterministic, sovereign, git-backed.

## Monorepo layout (npm workspaces)

| Package | Path | npm name | Purpose |
|---------|------|----------|---------|
| **Core** | `packages/core` | `@olonjs/core` | Runtime engine consumed by tenant apps |
| **CLI** | `packages/cli` | `@olonjs/cli` | Tenant scaffolding from DNA templates |
| **Stack** | `packages/stack` | `@olonjs/stack` | Version manifest for dependency alignment |
| **Tenant Alpha** | `apps/tenant-alpha` | — | Reference DNA template source (default) |
| **Tenant Agritourism** | `apps/tenant-agritourism` | — | Second DNA template source |

## Core / Tenant split (fundamental invariant)

**Core owns:** routing, `/admin`, `/admin/preview`, preview stage, studio state, inspector/form factory, engine behavior.

**Tenant owns:** sections (components), schemas, type augmentation, page/config JSON data, theme/design layer, workflow scripts.

The tenant does NOT implement the CMS. It implements the tenant protocol consumed by the engine.

## DNA generation (source of truth)

Template DNA is generated from source apps, never edited manually:

- `apps/tenant-alpha` -> `packages/cli/assets/templates/alpha/`
- `apps/tenant-agritourism` -> `packages/cli/assets/templates/agritourism/`

Commands:
- `npm run dist:dna:all` — regenerate all template DNA
- `npm run check:templates` — validate template conformance
- `npm run release:enterprise` — gated release (check + dist + publish)

## Build tools

- Vite 6 for core (library mode) and tenant apps
- `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `vite-plugin-dts`, `@tailwindcss/vite`
- TypeScript with ES2020 target, bundler module resolution
- Path alias: `@/*` -> `./src/*`

## Key specs and docs

- `specs/olonjsSpecs_V_1_5.md` — protocol specification (v1.5, normative for tenants / Studio)
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — monorepo architecture
- `docs/CLI.md` — CLI behavior and template resolution
- `docs/TEMPLATES.md` — template governance and DNA generation
- `docs/PUBLISHING.md` — publish/release operations

## CLI usage

```
npx @olonjs/cli new tenant <name> [--template <name>] [--agritourism]
```

Aliases: `olonjs` (primary), `jsonpages` (compatibility).

## Caveats

- On Windows UNC paths (`\\wsl.localhost\...`), npm/cmd may fail; use WSL shell.
- `scripts/release.js` only updates `tenant-alpha` dep pin during publish.
